{"title": "Boy, 12, charged with underage driving in Malaysia", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2024-08-08", "content": "A 12-year-old boy was charged in a Malaysian court on Aug 7 for underage driving, after a video of him driving a car around his neighbourhood with his two younger siblings in the vehicle sparked public outcry and a police investigation.\nHis father, a Pakistani national with Malaysian permanent resident status, was also charged, reported Malaysian media.\nThe boy, who was not named, was accused of driving a car in a residential area in the suburb of Puchong in Selangor on July 28.\nHe pleaded not guilty when the charge was read to him at the Sepang magistrate\u2019s court in the state of Selangor during a closed-door proceeding.\nIf found guilty, he could be fined up to RM2,000 (S$590), or face a maximum of six months\u2019 jail, or both.\nMeanwhile, his father, was charged with child neglect and for allowing an underage child to drive a vehicle.\nFor the charge of neglect, Muhammad Saleem Fazal Khuda, 53, faces up to 20 years\u2019 imprisonment or a maximum fine of RM50,000 or both, if convicted.\nFor the other charge, he could be fined up to RM2,000 or face a maximum of six months\u2019 jail or both.\nLawyer Nabilla Rosli, who represented both father and son, pleaded the court for a lower bail sum for the duo.\nThis is because Muhammad Saleem works as a carpet seller and earns an average of RM3,000 a month, said Ms Nabilla.\nOn top of that, he has to support his wife, who is a housewife, and five schoolgoing children aged between six and 19, she added.\nThe court allowed bail of RM500 for the boy and RM2,000 for the father.\nIt also set Sept 4 for the cases to be heard.\nIn the 90-second video that went viral, the boy could be seen driving a Perodua Viva car with two younger siblings, aged six and four, in the vehicle.\nIt then shows a woman, who is off-camera, flagging the car to stop.\nThe underage driver then winds down the car\u2019s front passenger window, and the woman asks for the ages of the boy and his siblings.\nShe also reprimands the underage driver, to which the boy responds by asking her to \u201cgo meet my father\u201d.\nIn reply, the woman says she will lodge a police report.\nThe children are not seen wearing seat belts in the video.\nPolice said the children were \u201cjoyriding\u201d in their neighbourhood."}